##  Setup Instructions

### 1️ Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/Manjeet300108/finance-backend
cd finance-backend

---

### 2️ Install Dependencies

npm install

---

### 3️ Configure Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file:

PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/financeDB
JWT_SECRET=secret123

---

### 4️ Run the Server

npm run dev

Server will run on:
http://localhost:5000

---

##  Authentication Flow

1. Register a user → `/auth/register`
2. Login → `/auth/login`
3. Receive JWT token
4. Use token in headers:

Authorization: "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpZCI6IjY5Y2Q1OTE1Y2Q1YzI5ZDBkN2NmYWQwYSIsInJvbGUiOiJhZG1pbiIsImlhdCI6MTc3NTA2NTk3M30.7aFJ1pylTUylT3vHQ8H_du4U3hqA67rXOyb8WehRZBc"

---

##  API Endpoints

###  Auth APIs

* POST /auth/register → Register user
* POST /auth/login → Login user

---

###  Record APIs

* GET /records → Get all records
* POST /records → Create record (**Admin only**)
* PUT /records/:id → Update record (**Admin only**)
* DELETE /records/:id → Delete record (**Admin only**)

---

###  Dashboard APIs

* GET /dashboard/summary → Get financial summary

---

##  API Testing

All APIs were tested using:

* **Thunder Client (VS Code Extension)** ⚡

This tool was used to:

* Send HTTP requests (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
* Test authentication using JWT tokens
* Validate API responses and error handling

---

##  Design Decisions

* MongoDB chosen for flexible schema and aggregation
* Modular architecture for scalability
* Middleware-based RBAC for clean access control
* JWT authentication for stateless security

---

## Assumptions

* Default role is **viewer**
* Admin privileges required for data modification
* Authentication required for protected routes

---

##  Future Improvements

* Pagination support
* Search functionality
* Swagger API documentation
* Unit & integration testing
* Deployment

---

##  Conclusion

This project demonstrates backend engineering fundamentals including API design, role-based access control, database modeling, and error handling.

