## 🔗 API Testing with Thunder Client (Detailed)

All APIs were tested using **Thunder Client (VS Code Extension)** ⚡.
Below are the exact routes and sample requests used during testing.

---

### 🔐 Auth APIs

#### ➤ Register User

POST /auth/register

Request Body:

```json
{
  "name": "Manu",
  "email": "manu@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456"
}
```

Response:

```json
{
  "_id": "user_id",
  "name": "Manu",
  "email": "manu@gmail.com",
  "role": "viewer"
}
```

---

#### ➤ Login User

POST /auth/login

Request Body:

```json
{
  "email": "manu@gmail.com",
  "password": "123456"
}
```

Response:

```json
{
  "token": "JWT_TOKEN"
}
```

---

### 🔐 Authorization Header

For protected routes, the following header was used:

Authorization: JWT_TOKEN

---

### 💰 Record APIs

#### ➤ Create Record (Admin Only)

POST /records

Request Body:

```json
{
  "amount": 5000,
  "type": "income",
  "category": "salary",
  "date": "2026-04-01",
  "notes": "monthly salary"
}
```

---

#### ➤ Get All Records

GET /records

---

#### ➤ Update Record

PUT /records/:id

---

#### ➤ Delete Record

DELETE /records/:id

---

### 📊 Dashboard API

#### ➤ Get Summary

GET /dashboard/summary

Response:

```json
{
  "totalIncome": 5000,
  "totalExpense": 0,
  "netBalance": 5000
}
```

---

### 🧪 Testing Workflow

1. User registered using `/auth/register`
2. Logged in via `/auth/login` to receive JWT token
3. Token added in headers for protected routes
4. Admin role assigned for testing record creation
5. All endpoints tested and validated using Thunder Client

